snippet.textDisplay: There is a way of re-doing things. For a comparison look at Afreen Afreen by Coke Studio PK, not losing the subtle beauty. For some reason this particular track is not pleasing to my ears. Not one bit. For that matter, even Ud. Shujaat Hussain Khan has sung it better while performing on sitar. To re-do , why is the need of drums and what is with the high tempo!!! You brought in tabla but it is barely audible in the dish and dhooms. Urgh! Such pleasing compositions have been presented by Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan ji, Shujaat Hussai Khan ji. These Coke Studio IN guys ruined it. Please dont spread the wrong word that new songs are crappy and these are good. You are adding to the crap by following the same scheme in music.
